Title:

THE SNOW ANGEL by Angela McAllister, Illustrated by Claire Fletcher

Description:

Elsa lies down in the snow and makes the shape of an angel. Her little brother, Jack, who was always dreaming, shuts his eyes and wishes more than anything else in the world that he could see a snow angel. And late that night when he looks out into the garden, he thinks he sees a shadowy shape.
